    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-01T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-01T22:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/4</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-01T22:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Suggestion made to the British Government through you has not been communicated
                    to any other government but the President asked you to let us know if there is
                    the slightest intimation that such a suggestion might be effective
                        elsewhere.<note n="1" xml:id="d59fn1">See the Ambassador’s telegram No. 258,
                        August 3, 6 p.m., <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_37">p.
                            37</ref>.</note> He is anxious to do everything in his power to avert
                    war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
